<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-01-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-01-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="371" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d371">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Meyer</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">St.
                                        Petersburg</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-01-01"><hi rend="italic">January 1,
                                1906</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Consul Smith in Moscow reports to-day by telephone that everything is
                            quieting down; barricades being removed; streets regaining normal
                            condition. American consulate has not been disturbed.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Meyer.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>